            <h2 id="unsplash-api-documentation">Unsplash API Documentation</h2>
            <p>Dive into Unsplash, a vast library offering royalty-free, high-resolution images. Enhance your projects without copyright concerns.</p>
            <p><strong>What Can I Use This API for?</strong></p>
            <ul>
            <li><p>Integrate beautiful visuals into your web or mobile applications.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Create stunning presentations, marketing materials, and blog posts.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Personalize user experiences with a wide variety of images.</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Getting Started</strong></p>
            <p>Get started by registering your application and obtaining an access key. This unlocks the power of the API.</p>
            <ol>
            <li><p><strong>Create a developer account with Unsplash.</strong> To create a developer account just go to <a href="https://unsplash.com/documentation">https://unsplash.com/documentation</a>.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p><strong>Register your application.</strong> This will help in authorization (provide an access token) for which you can access the API&#39;s full capability. A registered app goes into Demo Mode first with a limit of 50 requests per hour. Then later on one can apply for production mode. Demo mode is great for testing.</p>
            </li>
            </ol>
            <p><strong>Understanding Endpoints</strong></p>
            <p>Learn about available addresses and endpoints, allowing you to fetch specific content. The base URL for this API is <a href="https://api.unsplash.com/">https://api.unsplash.com/</a>. This is where all endpoints stem from and access different capabilities.</p>
            <ul>
            <li><p><strong>Photos Endpoint:</strong> Address is {{base_url}}/photos - This endpoint retrieves a collection of photos.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p><strong>Search Endpoint:</strong> Address is {{base_url}}/search/photos - This is the endpoint for searching for all photos depending on the query. It searches through queries provided. It can also take other query parameters which can be required or optional.</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Required parameters:</strong></p>
            <ul>
            <li>Query: search term</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Optional parameters:</strong></p>
            <ul>
            <li><p>Page</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Per_page</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Order_by</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Authorization</strong></p>
            <p>As with many APIs, the Unsplash API requires one to be authorized to access certain endpoints. Seamlessly integrate Unsplash using clear instructions on API authorization for calls.</p>
            <p>Unsplash uses access keys provided once you register your development app in their developer portal.</p>
            <ol>
            <li><p>Go to your registered application in your developer account.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Copy the access key associated with this application.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>The access key authorizes requests that require authorization to access.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>This access key can be used in two ways:</p>
            <ul>
            <li><p><strong>Authorization Header:</strong> Sent with every request.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p><strong>Query Parameter:</strong> Included in the request URL (e.g. {{base_url}}/photos?client_id={{access_key}}).</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ol>
