            <h2 id="rick-and-morty-api-documentation">Rick and Morty API Documentation</h2>
            <p>Get schwifty with the Rick and Morty API! Explore a vast collection of data about characters, locations, and episodes from the hit animated series Rick and Morty.</p>
            <p><strong>What can you do with this API?</strong></p>
            <ul>
            <li><p>Access detailed information about hundreds of Rick and Morty characters, including their names, statuses, species, and appearances.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Dive into various locations throughout the multiverse, uncovering their unique features and connections to characters.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Unravel the mysteries of the Rick and Morty universe by exploring episode details, air dates, and character appearances.</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Getting Started</strong></p>
            <p>The Rick and Morty API is a free and open-source RESTful API. To get started, you simply need to make HTTP requests to the API&#39;s base URL: <a href="https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/">https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/</a>. All responses are provided in JSON format.</p>
            <p><strong>Exploring Endpoints</strong></p>
            <p>The Rick and Morty API offers several endpoints for retrieving specific data:</p>
            <ul>
            <li><p><strong>Characters:</strong> /character - This endpoint retrieves a list of characters. You can optionally filter results by ID or name.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p><strong>Locations:</strong> /location - This endpoint retrieves a list of locations. You can optionally filter results by ID or name.</p>
            </li>
            <li><p><strong>Episodes:</strong> /episode - This endpoint retrieves a list of episodes. You can optionally filter results by ID or name.</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Example Requests:</strong></p>
            <ul>
            <li><p>Get information about character with ID 1: <a href="https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/character/1">https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/character/1</a></p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Get all locations containing the word &quot;Citadel&quot; in their name: <a href="https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/location?name=Citadel">https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/location?name=Citadel</a></p>
            </li>
            <li><p>Get the first 10 episodes: <a href="https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/episode?page=1&amp;per\_page=10">https://rickandmortyapi.com/api/episode?page=1&amp;per\_page=10</a></p>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Pagination:</strong></p>
            <p>For endpoints that return large datasets (like characters), the API uses pagination to manage the number of results returned per request. You can control pagination using the following query parameters:</p>
            <ul>
            <li><p>page: The current page number (defaults to 1).</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>per_page: The number of results per page (defaults to 20, maximum is 100).</p>
            </li>
            </ul>
